The paper discusses the detection of hardware Trojans in third party IPs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed technique is based on information flow security (IFS) verification, which involves analyzing the flow of information within a system, making it relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing Trojan detection techniques, which could be relevant to emerging technologies (cs.ET) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves understanding the behavior of malicious actors.
